'''Leshan Hall''', commonly known as '''Gaizhu Hall''', formerly known as '''Longshou Temple''', is located in China, [[:en:Fujian|Fujian Province]], [[:en:Ningde|Ningde City]], [[:en:Xiapu|Xiapu County]], {{ill|Baiyang Township|de|Baiyang Township|ja|柏洋郷|zh|柏洋乡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baiyang Township|qq=}}, {{ill|Tahu Village (Xiapu County)|de|Tahu-Dorf (Xiapu County)|ja|塔後村 (霞浦県)|zh|塔后村|lt=Tahu Village|lt_ja=塔後村|lt_de=Tahu-Dorf|lt_zh=塔后村|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tahu Village (Xiapu County)|qq=}} and {{ill|Shangwan Village (Xiapu County)|de|Shangwan-Dorf (Xiapu County)|ja|上万村 (霞浦県)|zh|上万村|lt=Shangwan Natural Village|lt_ja=上万自然村|lt_de=Shangwan-Naturdorf|lt_zh=上万自然村|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shangwan Village (Xiapu County)|qq=}}. It was established by Fujian {{ill|Mingjiao|de|Mingjiao|ja|明教|zh|明教|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mingjiao|qq=}} ([[:en:Manichaeism|Manichaeism]]) follower {{ill|Sun Mian|de|Sun Mian|ja|孫綿|zh|孙绵|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sun Mian|qq=}} during the {{ill|Northern Song|de|Nördliche Song-Dynastie|ja|北宋|zh|北宋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Northern Song|qq=}} period in the fourth year of {{ill|Qiande (Northern Song)|de|Qiande (Northern Song)|ja|乾德 (北宋)|zh|乾德|lt=Qiande|lt_ja=乾德|lt_de=Qiande|lt_zh=乾德|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Qiande (Northern Song)|qq=}} (966 AD), making it the earliest Manichaean building constructed in Fujian. For over a thousand years, it served as an important venue for Manichaean activities in the Baiyang area until it was destroyed in 2006 by {{ill|Typhoon Sangmei (2006)|de|Taifun Sangmei (2006)|ja|颱風桑美 (2006年)|zh|颱風桑美|lt=Sangmei Typhoon|lt_ja=桑美台風|lt_de=Sangmei-Taifun|lt_zh=桑美台风|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Typhoon Sangmei (2006)|qq=}}.
